'''Senate Act three-two-one, point seven (321.7)''' was a rule of the [[Senate Constitution]] enacted by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] circa [[18 BBY/Legends|18 BBY]]. It suspended the right of accused traitors of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] to choose one's own counsel in a court of law.

==Appearances==
*''[[The Last of the Jedi: A Tangled Web]]'' {{1st}}

